value.title: Biden’s inaugural address was ‘heartfelt appeal for unity’: Karl Rove
value.excerpt: Fox News contributor Karl Rove said Wednesday, President Joe Biden’s inaugural address was a “heartfelt appeal for unity.” Biden was sworn in as the 46th president of the United States and called for unity in his inaugural address amid a nation of political divide.

value.title: Biden reversing travel ban for Muslim countries ‘very disappointing’: Chad Wolf
value.excerpt: Former Acting Homeland Security Secretary Chad Wolf argued on Wednesday that President Biden’s intention to revoke Donald Trump's travel bans for majority-Muslim countries is "going to make the American people less safe."

value.title: Biden, Harris partake in Arlington wreath laying ceremony
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden and Vice President Kamala Harris, after being sworn in at the Capitol, traveled to Arlington National Cemetery for a ceremony at the Tomb of the Unknown Soldier.

value.title: Marco Rubio rejects Biden immigration bill, calls it ‘blanket amnesty’
value.excerpt: Sen. Marco Rubio, R-Fla., on Tuesday rejected an immigration proposal by President Biden, describing its call for an 8-year pathway to citizenship for illegal immigrants as a “blanket amnesty.”

value.title: Sotomayor mispronounces Kamala Harris' name – Twitter reacts
value.excerpt: Supreme Court Justice Sonia Sotomayor on Wednesday botched the pronunciation of Kamala Harris’ name during her swearing-in as the nation’s next Vice President – and the Twittersphere was quick to pounce on the mistake.

value.title: Pelosi says Trump could be 'accessory to murder' in connection with Capitol riot
value.excerpt: House Speaker Nancy Pelosi said former President Donald Trump could be considered an accessory to murder in connection with this month's deadly riot at the U.S. Capitol.

value.title: Pence skips Trump send-off where outgoing president thanks him, attends Biden inauguration
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence attended President-elect Joe Biden's inaugural ceremony on Wednesday after skipping President Trump's farewell address at Joint Base Andrews.

value.title: Racism allowed Donald Trump 'free rein to terrorize the American people for four years:' MSNBC analyst
value.excerpt: New York Times editorial board member Mara Gay said Wednesday that President Trump had been allowed to "terrorize the American people for four years" because of racist elements in the country.

value.title: Melania Trump says serving as first lady was 'my greatest honor'
value.excerpt: Melania Trump told a small crowd of supporters Wednesday that it was "my greatest honor" to serve as the first lady.

value.title: Donald Trump pardons, commutes Lil Wayne, Kodak Black sentences prompting reactions from fans and critics
value.excerpt: Donald Trump has issued a pardon and sentence commutation to rappers Lil Wayne and Kodak Black ahead of Joe Biden's inauguration. President Trump issued 73 pardons and 70 sentence commutations early Wednesday as he prepared to leave office.

value.title: Snoop Dogg praises Trump for commuting sentence of Death Row Record co-founder Michael 'Harry O' Harris
value.excerpt: Snoop Dogg praised President Trump in his final hours in office for commuting the sentence of his friend, Death Row Records co-founder Michael "Harry O" Harris.

value.title: Sen. Cotton tears into Biden’s ‘radical immigration agenda’: ‘what you’d expect from the party of open borders
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden is expected to unveil a sweeping immigration plan during his early days in office, which will aim to reverse Trump-era policies – but his proactive approach is garnering pushback from both sides of the aisle.

value.title: Graham warns border will be 'overrun’ unless Biden sends ‘clear and unmistakable signal’ to migrant caravans
value.excerpt: Sen. Lindsey Graham, R-S.C., on Tuesday warned that the U.S. border will be “overrun” unless the incoming Biden administration sends a message to the incoming migrant caravans that they support President Donald Trump’s policies on immigration.

value.title: Biden DNI nominee Haines says aim should be to 'out-compete China'
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden's nominee for Director of National Intelligence Avril Haines said, if confirmed, she would focus on providing intelligence to support efforts to "out-compete China," while committing to doing more training to educate Americans on the country's malign foreign influence.

value.title: Tiffany Trump announces engagement to Michael Boulos with White House photo, hours before father leaves office
value.excerpt: President Trump's youngest daughter Tiffany Trump and her beau Michael Boulos announced their engagement with a photo taken at the White House on the president's last day in office.

value.title: Army veteran calls out Dem lawmaker for ‘ridiculous’ remark about troops posing threat to Biden
value.excerpt: A West Point graduate and Army veteran ripped Rep. Steve Cohen, D-Tenn., for floating the conspiracy theory that National Guard troops deployed to Washington, D.C., for the inauguration pose a threat to President-elect Joe Biden.

value.title: Wyoming Republicans censure Cheney over Trump impeachment vote
value.excerpt: Wyoming's Carbon County Republican Party voted unanimously to censure Rep. Liz Cheney, R-Wyo., for voting with nine other House Republicans to impeach President Trump on charges of "incitement of an insurrection."

value.title: Huckabee pushes back on calls for 'deprogramming' Trump voters: 'The cult of the left'
value.excerpt: In response to some people claiming Trump supporters need to be "deprogrammed," Fox News contributor Mike Huckabee on Tuesday explained why people voted for the former reality TV star to lead the country.

value.title: Trump rebuts NY Times '1619 Project' with '1776 Report' urging schools to reject 'ideological poison'
value.excerpt: The Trump-backed panel released a 45-page report on the state of American education in what the White House described as a "rebuttal" to "reckless" historical accounts of the country's founding.

value.title: Trump National Garden order includes statues of Whitney Houston, Kobe Bryant, Vince Lombardi, Frank Sinatra
value.excerpt: President Trump issued an executive order on Monday in which he listed dozens of "historically significant" Americans, including entertainers, founding fathers, religious figures, and others, to be featured in the new National Garden of American Heroes.

value.title: Disgraced ex-Baltimore mayor wants Trump to commute her sentence
value.excerpt: Catherine Pugh, the disgraced former Baltimore mayor convicted of using her book sales to help fund a political career, is reportedly among those seeking clemency from President Donald Trump before he leaves office.

value.title: Biden’s reported plans to kill Keystone XL pipeline alarm Canadian officials
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden is considering canceling the cross-border permit for TC energy’s Keystone XL pipeline -- and Canadian officials are worried.

value.title: Biden aims to 'Make America California Again': paper
value.excerpt: The Los Angeles Times ran a headline Sunday that is sure to grab the attention of Trump supporters everywhere: “Make America California Again? That’s Biden’s plan.”

value.title: AOC says she disagrees with Biden's 'optimistic' view of GOP
value.excerpt: Rep. Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez said she disagrees with President-elect Biden on his “optimistic” view of the GOP.

value.title: 'What the hell is wrong with them?': Biden rips Republicans for refusing to don masks during siege
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden is taking aim at some Republican members of Congress who refused to wear masks while huddling in secure rooms last week during the storming of the Capitol.

value.title: FBI agent in Trump-Russia's request for 'validation' of Steele reporting denied, left Crossfire Hurricane
value.excerpt: An agent involved in the FBI’s original Trump-Russia case left the Crossfire Hurricane team amid a “professional disagreement” with Bill Priestap, after the former assistant director of counterintelligence denied his request for an “enhanced validation review” of Christopher Steele’s reporting.
